# Reverse-proxy example.
#
# Default deployment (Docker Compose in this repo) runs a single `rag` service
# (english-v1-rag/app.py on port 5002) that serves BOTH:
#   - /       → full multilingual corpus
#   - /beta   → English-only beta
# In that mode you don't need any path-based routing here — just proxy
# everything to the rag service.
#
# If you ever run them as two separate processes:
#   - main-rag:  scripts/rag/app.py      (port 5001) — full corpus only at /
#   - beta-rag:  english-v1-rag/app.py   (port 5002) — English at / (without /beta prefix)
# you can split with `handle /beta/*` blocks and `uri strip_prefix /beta`.

{$DOMAIN:localhost} {
	reverse_proxy rag:5002
}
